  "prompt": "What are the must watch Hollywood movies before you die (count not more than 10)?",
  "response": "Creating a list of must-watch Hollywood movies is inherently subjective, but the following ten films are widely acclaimed for their storytelling, direction, cultural impact, and enduring legacy. Watching these classics will give you a broad appreciation of the evolution and artistry of Hollywood cinema.\n\n1. **The Godfather (1972)**\n   - *Director:* Francis Ford Coppola\n   - *Why Watch:* Often cited as one of the greatest films ever made, this epic tale of family, power, and betrayal offers standout performances and masterful storytelling.\n\n2. **Citizen Kane (1941)**\n   - *Director:* Orson Welles\n   - *Why Watch:* Renowned for its innovative narrative structure and cinematography, this film explores the complexities of power and legacy.\n\n3. **Casablanca (1942)**\n   - *Director:* Michael Curtiz\n   - *Why Watch:* A timeless romantic drama set against the backdrop of World War II, celebrated for its memorable characters and iconic lines.\n\n4. **Schindler's List (1993)**\n   - *Director:* Steven Spielberg\n   - *Why Watch:* A powerful and poignant depiction of the Holocaust, this film is acclaimed for its emotional depth and historical significance.\n\n5. **Pulp Fiction (1994)**\n   - *Director:* Quentin Tarantino\n   - *Why Watch:* Known for its non-linear narrative and sharp dialogue, this film revolutionized indie cinema and influenced a generation of filmmakers.\n\n6. **The Shawshank Redemption (1994)**\n   - *Director:* Frank Darabont\n   - *Why Watch:* A moving story of hope and friendship set in a prison, often ranked highly by audiences for its inspirational message.\n\n7. **Star Wars: Episode IV \u2013 A New Hope (1977)**\n   - *Director:* George Lucas\n   - *Why Watch:* A groundbreaking science fiction adventure that spawned a massive franchise and changed the landscape of blockbuster filmmaking.\n\n8. **Gone with the Wind (1939)**\n   - *Director:* Victor Fleming\n   - *Why Watch:* An epic historical romance known for its grand scale, memorable performances, and cultural impact on American cinema.\n\n9. **The Dark Knight (2008)**\n   - *Director:* Christopher Nolan\n   - *Why Watch:* A superhero film that transcends genre expectations with its complex characters, moral dilemmas, and stunning action sequences.\n\n10. **Forrest Gump (1994)**\n    - *Director:* Robert Zemeckis\n    - *Why Watch:* This heartwarming tale follows an endearing protagonist through pivotal moments in American history, blending humor, drama, and romance.\n\n### Honorable Mentions\n\n- **Inception (2010)** \u2013 A mind-bending thriller that explores dreams and reality.\n- **Fight Club (1999)** \u2013 A gritty exploration of society and identity.\n- **Titanic (1997)** \u2013 A romantic epic set against the ill-fated voyage of the RMS Titanic.\n- **The Matrix (1999)** \u2013 A revolutionary sci-fi film that delves into virtual reality and human consciousness.\n\nThese films represent a mix of genres, eras, and styles, offering a comprehensive overview of Hollywood's cinematic achievements. Watching them will provide insight into storytelling techniques, thematic depth, and the evolution of filmmaking.",
